last_episode_to_air.name: It's a Hard Doc Life
last_episode_to_air.overview: After making a big mistake at the McStuffinsville Toy Hospital, Doc begins to wonder if her patients would have been better off if she hadn't been there at all.

name: Doc McStuffins
overview: A young African-American girl aspires to be a doctor like her mom.

episodes.name: Knight Time
episodes.overview:
Doc discovers that Donny's toy knight, Sir Kirby, is dirty.

Song: Ba-Ba Bubbles!

episodes.name: A Bad Case of the Pricklethorns
episodes.overview:
Doc diagnoses Boppy, a toy dog bopping bag, when he suddenly gets popped after landing in a rose bush.

Song: Bop, Bop, Bop (Don't Wanna Pop)

episodes.name: Out of the Box
episodes.overview:
Little Jack, a jack in the box, can't pop, but he's scared of getting a check-up, so his dad, Big Jack, goes first.

Song: Pop Up

episodes.name: Run Down Race Car
episodes.overview:
Ricardo Racecar loses his energy during a race. Then, Doc and the gang need to recharge it.

Song: Get Your Sleep On

episodes.name: Tea Party Tantrum
episodes.overview:
Doc wonders why Susie Sunshine, a doll, is acting very cranky.

Song: Close Your Eyes

episodes.name: Blast Off!
episodes.overview:
Doc helps Carlos' toy space alien, Star Blazer Zero after his arms and legs fall off after a crash in his toy rocket.

Song: Be Safe!

Sickness: Broken parts

episodes.name: Engine Nine, Feelin' Fine!
episodes.overview:
Donny thinks that his toy fire engine Lenny, a.k.a. Engine 9, is broken, when it actually ran out of water in his holding tanks, so Doc refills him.

Song: Water, Water

Sickness: Dehydration (Dry-out)

episodes.name: The Right Stuff
episodes.overview: During an adventure game, Stuffy's tail gets ripped, but he won't ask for help and soon it gets worse as he loses more stuffing from his tail.

episodes.name: Gulpy, Gulpy Gators!
episodes.overview:
Doc fixes Gustave, the green gator on Donny's Gulpy Gulpy Gators game after he eats too many marbles.

Song: Be Good To Your Tummy

episodes.name: One Note Wonder
episodes.overview:
Alma's xylophone toy, Xyla, loses a key by accident while being repaired for a loose screw.

Song: Rocking The Right Note

episodes.name: Arcade Escapade
episodes.overview:
Doc helps a stuffed toy Giraffe called Gaby after her leg was torn in an accident in the claw crane machine at the arcade.

Song: Nobody Wants A Broken Toy

episodes.name: Starry, Starry Night
episodes.overview:
Doc helps Henry's Telescope Aurora when she suffers from blurry vision.

Song: Stars, Stars (Planets, Stars And Galaxies)

episodes.name: Ben/Anna Split
episodes.overview:
Ben and Anna, Alma's "Huggy Monkeys" need to be separated after one of them suffered a torn Velcro "hug" patch and needed to recover overnight at the clinic.

Song: We're Ben-Anna

Sickness: Torn Velcro patch

episodes.name: That's Just Claw-ful
episodes.overview:
Doc helps Hermie, her toy crab, after his arm was torn out by Emmie and Alma's new puppy Rudi.

Song: You Can Do It!

Sickness: Torn arm

episodes.name: A Good Case of the Hiccups
episodes.overview:
Doc tries to fix Millie the Microphone when she can't stop repeating words.

Song: If You Got The Hiccups

Sickness: Repeatitis

episodes.name: Stuck Up
episodes.overview:
When Doc accidentally gets sand in her eye, she finds out what's wrong with Will's toy digger, Riggo, when his scoop gets stuck.

Song: Dig, Dig, Dig

Sickness: Stuck Scooper

episodes.name: Rescue Ronda, Ready for Take-off
episodes.overview:
Doc has to fix Luca's helicopter, Rescue Ronda, when she can't fly, due to getting a little twig from a bush in her propeller.

Song: When You Need A Friend

episodes.name: All Washed Up
episodes.overview:
Donny's toy robot, Robot Ray, learns the importance of following doctor's orders when he gets wet playing a game.

Song: Do What The Doctor Says

episodes.name: The New Girl
episodes.overview:
Doc gets an "action toy" doll from Japan from her grandmother called Kiko, and emphasizes exercise when she finds out that Kiko has weak legs.

Song: Ready For Action

episodes.name: Wrap it Up
episodes.overview:
Niles, Donny's toy crane, refuses to have his old bandages removed when they start unraveling.

Song: In A Flash

Sickness: Y.O.B. Itis (Yucky Old Bandage Itis)

episodes.name: Rest Your Rotors, Ronda!
episodes.overview:
Rescue Ronda learns how good it is to rest when her propeller is broken and needs time to heal.

Song: Rest Your Rotors, Ronda!

episodes.name: Keep on Truckin'
episodes.overview:
Donny's toy truck, Tremaine, learns how to keep still to get repainted.

Song: Keep Still

episodes.name: Blame it on the Rain
episodes.overview:
Alma accidentally leaves her stuffed cow Moo Moo outside during a downpour and Doc fixes her, but she refuses to go home when she believes her owner doesn't like her.

Song: Nobody's Perfect (Forgive And Forget)

episodes.name: Busted Boomer
episodes.overview:
Boomer, Emmie's deflated Soccer ball refuses to be reinflated due to having a fear of needles.

Song: Here For You

episodes.name: Dark Knight
episodes.overview:
During a sleepover party, Doc discovers that Sir Kirby is afraid of the dark and cures him of his fear.

Song: We Can Light The Night

episodes.name: Hallie Gets an Earful
episodes.overview:
Doc helps Hallie hear better after she has trouble hearing.

Song: Have You Heard?

episodes.name: Break Dancer
episodes.overview: Bella, Doc's Ballerina doll, breaks her leg, and finds a lot to do while she waits for it to heal.

episodes.name: Bubble Monkey
episodes.overview: Doc examines Emmie and Alma's bubble monkey after she stops blowing bubbles.

episodes.name: Out in the Wild
episodes.overview: Doc helps Robot Ray after he injures his arm after being abducted by a bluebird during a camping trip. Doc later refers to having gotten a case of Panicitic in response to the situation, and of this being her first surgery

episodes.name: A Whale of a Time
episodes.overview: Doc helps Lula, the sponge Beluga Whale toy grow.

episodes.name: The Rip Heard Round the World
episodes.overview: Lambie accidentally gets ripped while dancing with Doc.

episodes.name: Walkie-Talkie Time
episodes.overview: Doc reunites a walkie talkie couple, Walter and Gracie, by finding Walter's missing antenna.

episodes.name: Un-Bur-Able
episodes.overview: While playing Astronautball, Stuffy falls into a bush and get burrs all over his body.

episodes.name: Righty-on-Lefty
episodes.overview: Doc helps Awesome Guy, a toy superhero, after she discovers that he couldn't walk correctly.

episodes.name: Hallie's Happy BIrthday
episodes.overview: It's Hallie's birthday and Doc and the gang throw a surprise party in her honor.

episodes.name: Shark-Style Toothache
episodes.overview: Mr. Chomp, Donny's toy shark, has a broken tooth that needs to repaired, but everyone (except for Doc and Hallie) are afraid of him because of his sharp teeth.

episodes.name: Awesome Possums
episodes.overview: Penny's baby, a Toy possum named Pip is lost and Doc and the others frantically searches the house for Pip and reunites it with its mother.

episodes.name: The Bunny Blues
episodes.overview: Doc discovers Alma's stuffed bunny, Pickles, in a box at a yard sale, but she doesn't have a nose so Doc tries to find a perfect nose for her.

episodes.name: Get Set to Get Wet
episodes.overview: Doc finds a mermaid doll called Mermaid Melinda in the wading pool and teaches her how to swim.

episodes.name: Loud Louie
episodes.overview: A toy cellphone, Louie, has a slight problem with his volume switch, causing him to talk real loud.

episodes.name: Caught Blue-Handed
episodes.overview: After Donny and Glo-Bo finish finger-painting an "elephant eating blueberries", a mysterious blue rash infects all the toys in the clinic and Doc needs to figure out about what is causing it.

episodes.name: To Squeak, or Not to Squeak
episodes.overview: Marvin the Duck lost his squeaker during the water fight at the water park and it's up to Doc, Lambie and Stuffy to find it.

episodes.name: Doctoring the Doc
episodes.overview: It is sick day for Doc and the crew from the Clinic helps Doc get plenty of rest.

episodes.name: Hot Pursuit
episodes.overview: A metal toy police car, Officer Pete, overheats while pursuing the Wicked King.

episodes.name: Boo-Hoo to You!
episodes.overview: On Halloween, Doc helps a toy ghost, Sebastian, learn not to be scared of the decorations.

episodes.name: It's Glow Time
episodes.overview: Glo-Bo is very tired, weak and unable to glow. So Doc and her toys need to find a way to get him back his glowing effect.

episodes.name: Chilly Gets Chilly
episodes.overview: Doc is excited to play outside in the snow. Then, Chilly decides to hang out with the snowman that the gang built but nearly freezes in the cold.

episodes.name: Through the Reading Glasses
episodes.overview: Doc receives a stuffed toy owl named Professor Hootsburgh from her older cousin, but she can't read properly because of her poor eyesight.

episodes.name: My Huggy Valentine
episodes.overview: Lambie becomes jealous and brokenhearted when Val, a new toy, steals the spotlight from her during the Valentine's Day party at the clinic.

episodes.name: Dusty Bear
episodes.overview: A teddy bear named Teddy B. discovers why Donny doesn't want to play with Teddy B

episodes.name: Bronto Boo-Boos
episodes.overview: When Bronty, a toy Brontosaurus arrives to the McStuffins household, a mysterious outbreak of injuries affects the other toys due to Bronty playing roughly with them and not realizing it.

episodes.name: Brontosaurus Breath
episodes.overview: Doc and the gang wonder why Bronty has a bad case of bad breath so they teach Bronty how to brush his teeth to make it smell nice.

episodes.name: Doc McStuffins Goes McMobile
episodes.overview: After discovering that she couldn't fix Maddie's toy mouse, Norton, in the park, Doc's dad builds a mobile clinic for her to fix toys when she's away from her clinic.

episodes.name: Chip Off the Ol' Box
episodes.overview: While practicing their Juggling Jacks Act for Buddy's birthday party, Big Jack hurts his crank after Donny crashes into him while practicing some defensive soccer save moves, leaving him unable to perform.

episodes.name: Awesome Guy's Awesome Arm
episodes.overview: Awesome Guy injures his arm while showing off his awesome strength and Doc orders him to rest up.

episodes.name: Lamb in a Jam
episodes.overview: Lambie got covered with jam while being placed into Doc's backpack due to a faulty sandwich bag. Before going with her to school on "Take Your Toy To School Day", Lambie felt sad and bitter about not going to school with Doc. So, she covered Stuffy who was to take her place for "Take Your Toy To School Day" in jam as well preventing him from going to school with Doc.

episodes.name: Diagnosis Not Even Close-Is
episodes.overview: Doc takes the afternoon off from the clinic to help train Emmie's dog Rudi with a new agility training center that Emmie's family bought. So, Stuffy and Hallie fill in as doctors while trying to find out why Robot Ray is going out of control. The toys call Doc for help and she succeeds to find the real problem.

episodes.name: Bronty's Twisted Tail
episodes.overview: Doc creates a musical group but Bronty injures his tail after Stuffy crashes into him.

episodes.name: Frida Fairy Flies Again
episodes.overview: Frida Fairy, a fairy-shaped kite who thinks she's a real fairy, rips her wing after crashing into a tree branch and Doc tries to repair her.

episodes.name: A Tale of Two Dragons
episodes.overview: Dragon-Bot, a new state of the art robotic toy dragon, has a problem with his wings popping out and Doc checks what is causing the problem but Stuffy becomes jealous over Dragon-Bot being more hi-tech than him.

episodes.name: Think Pink
episodes.overview: Chilly turns pink from Doc's red scarf after being accidentally washed in the washing machine by Doc's dad.

episodes.name: You Foose, You Lose
episodes.overview: The other players in the Foosball court are ready to play but Johnny Foosball isn't ready because he is suffering from a sticking problem and is reluctant to tell his teammates about it.

episodes.name: Leilani's Luau
episodes.overview: Doc receives a solar powered hula girl named Leilani from her grandmother, but she feels a little homesick for her home in Hawaii so Doc throws a Luau for her.

episodes.name: Karate Kangaroos
episodes.overview: Doc helps Angus, a Karate Kangaroo who doesn't want to fight Sidney, his partner, because of his fear of fighting.

episodes.name: Doc to the Rescue
episodes.overview: Doc discovers a fashion doll named Dress-Up Daisy stuck in a tree and tries to calm her down from panicking while rescuing her.

episodes.name: Don't Knock the Noggin
episodes.overview: Doc helps an action figure named Super Stuntman Steve after he starts malfunctioning for losing his helmet.

episodes.name: Disco Dress Up Daisy
episodes.overview: Disco Dress Up Daisy injures her arm while showboating on roller skates and gets a fashionable pink cast for her arm and Lambie becomes envious and tries to fake an injury to get a cast for herself. Doc diagnoses her with "I want a boo-boo syndrome" and relates to having had it in the past when her friend Emmie had a cast.

episodes.name: The Glider Brothers
episodes.overview: The Glider Brothers, two planes named Orville and Wilbur (after the Wright brothers), fly recklessly around the McStuffins household resulting in Wilbur breaking the rubber band that powers his propeller.

episodes.name: Kirby and the King
episodes.overview: Sir Kirby and The Wicked King get stuck together with paste after battling with Donny's cardboard monster, so they try to get unstuck.

episodes.name: Bubble Monkey, Blow Your Nose!
episodes.overview: Doc brings Bubble Monkey to visit Donny to cheer him up after he catches a cold, but Bubble Monkey has a sneezing fit that spreads soap bubble liquid all over the place.

episodes.name: Professor Pancake
episodes.overview: Doc rescues Professor Hootsburgh after being accidentally trapped behind Doc's toy box and was accidentally flattened.

episodes.name: You Crack Me Up
episodes.overview: Gloria the Giggling Gorilla, Donny's new toy, keeps scratching her belly, so Doc investigates the cause of her itch.

episodes.name: A Very McStuffins Christmas
episodes.overview: An elf named Tobias needs help after accidentally breaking Donny's new toy, Commander Crush, so Doc and her friends go to the North Pole to get a new part. However, Stuffy gets separated from the group, so its up to Lambie and Chilly to rescue him.

episodes.name: The Doctor Will See You Now
episodes.overview: Dolly, Morton, Carl Chug a Chug, and Fabio, the toys in the waiting room at the doctor's office, receive a check up by Doc after wondering why the children in the clinic don't want to play them. This is the first instance of Doc being called Dottie in the show.

episodes.name: L'il Egghead Feels the Heat
episodes.overview: Professor Hootsburgh challenges Eggie, an electronic learning device, to a face-off to see who's the smartest toy in the McStuffins Household, but Eggie overheats and starts malfunctioning.

episodes.name: The Big Sleepover
episodes.overview: Doc becomes homesick during a sleepover at Emmie and Alma's house, so Stuffy, Lambie and Pickles try to cheer her up.

episodes.name: No Sweetah Cheetah
episodes.overview: Chilly and the other toys think that Rita, Donny's toy cheetah, is sick because of her spots, but Doc later discovers that she doesn't have an illness. Rita's spots are a part of her physical features.

episodes.name: Big Head Hallie
episodes.overview: Hallie discovers that she was based on a popular cartoon character and lets it go into her head.

episodes.name: Peaches Pie, Take a Bath!
episodes.overview: Peaches Pie, a cute peach scented doll, refuses to take a bath but doesn't realize that her peachy smell is gone thanks to Rudy playing with her in the rain.

episodes.name: Celestial Celeste
episodes.overview: Celeste, Doc's space projector toy from school is having trouble working by making a strange whirring noise after nearly getting knock off the shelf by Stuffy. So it's up to Doc and the gang to fix it.

episodes.name: Run Doc Run!
episodes.overview: Doc sprains her ankle during a practice run for a Fun Run while trying to avoid a toy unicorn that was laying on the sidewalk. Doc has to rest, so the toys have to cure Doc and Doc has to cure Dart the Unicorn's broken leg before she does. This is the second instance of Doc being called Dottie.

episodes.name: A Fairy Big Knot
episodes.overview: Frida the Fairy Flier's strings gets knotted up during a very windy day and crashes and it's up to Doc to detangle her strings.

episodes.name: Rosie the Rescuer
episodes.overview: Rosie the Rescuer, Emmie and Alma's toy EMT ambulance, panics while trying to save Sir Kirby. Later, Doc helps Rosie to calm down and not to panic by telling of her past experience helping Robot Ray.

episodes.name: Crikey! It's Wildlife Will
episodes.overview: Wildlife Will, a toy explorer, loses his legs after a run in with a Chihuahua and it's up to Doc and company to build a special wheelchair for him.

episodes.name: Rootin' Tootin' Southwest Sal
episodes.overview: Southwest Sal, a toy cowgirl that is literally a cow, has a broken spring which controls her lasso throwing arm, and it's up to Doc to fix her.

episodes.name: Take Your Doc To Work Day
episodes.overview: On "Take Your Child To Work Day" Doc helps out at her mom's clinic by giving physicals to The Waiting Room Toys and helps a doll named Curly-Q fix her hair by giving her a new hair style.

episodes.name: Blazer's Bike
episodes.overview: Star Blazer Zero has a problem riding his bike by crashing into everything and discovered that he had a helmet for a football player instead of his space helmet.

episodes.name: The Big Storm
episodes.overview: A hurricane hits the neighborhood and Doc helps create an evacuation plan for the toys in the clinic including a "buddy system" but Chilly and Hallie accidentally get left behind when Chilly falls off the wagon during the evacuation and Hallie tries to help keep him calm.

episodes.name: Spritzy Mitzi
episodes.overview: Spritzy Mitzi, an octopus shaped sprinkler toy, ruptures a sprinkler tentacle after getting a pebble stuck in one of her sprinkling holes after ignoring Stuffy's advice on having Doc checking it out first.

episodes.name: Dad's Favorite Toy
episodes.overview: While cleaning out the attic Doc's Dad finds a beloved toy from his childhood called Saltwater Serge and Wellington Whale. Serge and Wellington don't work because their button is worn out after being used a lot by Doc's Dad when he was young.

episodes.name: Chilly and the Dude
episodes.overview: Chilly meets up with a stuffed snowman known as "The Dude" when Doc goes to the clinic to make winter gift baskets for a school charity drive. Chilly is jealous when he feels that The Dude is more charming and athletic than him but learns that it's ok to be yourself.

episodes.name: Serpent Sam Makes a Splash
episodes.overview: Doc diagnoses Serpent Sam, a cool new snake shaped super soaker water gun toy, who is suffering from "Sticky-it is" after he fills up with green apple soda instead of his usual water and gets clogged up from the sticky sugar residue.

episodes.name: Sir Kirby and the Plucky Princess
episodes.overview: To prove that princesses can do anything knights can do, Princess Persephone, or "Peri," as she likes to be called, challenges Sir Kirby to a playoff competition. Problems arise when Sir Kirby falls apart during the wall scaling competition after losing his balance and slamming himself against the castle wall.

episodes.name: The Wicked King and the Mean Queen
episodes.overview: A snobbish new doll named Queen Amina arrives to the McStuffins household and start to lock horns with The Wicked King over who should throw the first Royal Ball. So Doc and the crew decided to have a treasure hunt for the two to see who gets the most coins wins the rights to host the Royal Ball. But when Queen Amina injures herself during the competition, the Wicked King decided that friendship and sportsmanship was more important than winning.

episodes.name: Take a Stroll!
episodes.overview: After losing a relay race, Alma's baby doll Tiny Tessie discovers that she needs to get out of her Sleepy Slumber 2000 Stroller to be active and have more fun.

episodes.name: Ooey Gablooey Springs a Leak
episodes.overview: Oooey Gablooey, a toy sticky starfish which Donny won at the school fair, accidentally punctures himself after landing in a rose bush and started leaking blue ooze all over and panics after seeing his goo leaking out as Doc tries to repair him.

episodes.name: There's a King in Your Tummy!
episodes.overview: While at the park, Serpent Sam accidentally swallows the Wicked King while filling up with water and Doc and the crew try to figure out a way to get the Wicked King out of Serpent Sam's tummy safely.

episodes.name: Doc's Busy Day
episodes.overview: Doc learns how to triage her patients after becoming overwhelmed with a busy day at the clinic when her and Donny's talking toddler cousin Sabrina comes for a visit to the McStuffins household and causes chaos and a whole lot of boo-boos for the toys.

episodes.name: Wrong Side of the Law
episodes.overview: Princess Doc and Princess Lamby are having a tea party when a police car interrupts them. Doc helps Officer Pete recognize that his eyesight is being hindered by a dirty and cracked windshield after wrecking while pursuing Kent during a high speed pursuit and needed a replacement windshield.

episodes.name: Mirror, Mirror on My Penguin
episodes.overview: Baby Suki's toy penguin Waddly is upset because she doesn't want to play with her and Doc discovers that the mirror in Waddly's tummy was dirty with baby guck.

episodes.name: Hide and Eek!
episodes.overview: While playing Mad Scientist, Professor Donny and Professor Alma "create" a toy monster named Creepy Cuddly Charlie that scares all the other toys (except for Doc and Hallie). When they finally get to know Charlie, they realized that he's not that scary.

episodes.name: McStuffins School of Medicine
episodes.overview: Dr Tundra, Emmie's new teddy bear learns about the medical profession from Doc as a intern in her clinic and helps Stuffy after he crushed his snout in a book avalanche.

episodes.name: The Super Amazing Ultra Hoppers
episodes.overview: Delloroto one of the Super Amazing Ultra Hoppers couldn't jump high like his brothers DiNardo and DiAmbrosio. So Doc (or "Dottoressa" as she was called) discovers that Delloroto was missing a few bricks making him shorter than his brothers.

episodes.name: Let the Nightingale Sing
episodes.overview: Doc and the toys time travel back to 19th century England and they meet a young Florence Nightingale (Hallie's favorite idol) and help Florence accomplish her dream to be a nurse and assist her in repairing her toys.

episodes.name: Hazel Has a Sleepover
episodes.overview: Before Doc and Emmie have a pre-sleepover water fight at the McStuffins residence Hazel, Emmie's new water toy, has a slight sleepwetting problem (leaky trunk) and Doc tries to solve her problem. She is diagnosed with too-full-itis.

episodes.name: My Breakfast with Bronty
episodes.overview: During breakfast, Bronty accidentally knocks over and stomps on a bottle of syrup which splashed onto his rear legs and caused his rear legs to be stuck onto his tail, but Bronty was reluctant to tell Doc about his situation.

episodes.name: Training Army Al
episodes.overview: Doc tells her friends including a worrisome Bronty to feel their emotions when Army Al, an action figure, is separated from them after being called for duty, even if it's a trip to the forest with Donny and his Turtle Scouts troop. Doc and the toys support each other and help prepare Al to be his best because they are afraid that something bad might happen to him.

episodes.name: Sproingo Boingo Takes the Leap
episodes.overview: A fox shaped Slinky toy named Sproingo Boingo accidentally twists his spring after doing a dangerous leap from a tall block tower for the Wicked King during a rainy day competition. So it was up to Doc to fix Sproingo Boingo but the Wicked King felt bad for causing his injury and daring him to do a dangerous leap but Sproingo Boingo said that it was okay and accepted his apology.

episodes.name: Shell Shy
episodes.overview: A wind up toy Sea Turtle named Theodore is extremely shy after that discovering that Hermie who was a old friend from the aquarium (and the most popular toy at the aquarium) was living at Doc's and is the grand Splash Dance champion. So Doc and Company helps Theodore overcome his shyness.

episodes.name: Commander No
episodes.overview: During a game of Tickle Tag with Gloria the Giggling Gorilla, Commander Crush starts to malfunction and couldn't stop transforming. Doc discovers that Commander Crush had a stuck button that caused him to malfunction but now Commander Crush refuses to play the Tickle Game fearing that he'll malfunction again.

episodes.name: The Flimsy Grumpy Bat
episodes.overview: The toys teach Count Clarence the Magnificent, a cardboard bat who thinks he could fly like a kite about good positive attitudes after he becomes grumpy from getting caught in a gust of wind and crashing into the wading pool at the park.

episodes.name: Rockstar Ruby and the Toys
episodes.overview: Doc purchase a used Rock Star doll named Rockstar Ruby at a Yard Sale but as dirt and gunk builds up over time while being played at and eventually causes Rockstar Ruby's microphone button to get stuck forcing her to quit singing. But Doc and the crew has a plan to bring back Rockstar Ruby back on stage.

episodes.name: A Day Without Cuddles!
episodes.overview: It's International Cuddle Day at the clinic but Lambie suffered from a mysterious sneezing fit. Doc discovered that Lambie was covered with flour and ordered Lambie to be quarantined and not to give out any cuddles.

episodes.name: Collide-O-Scope
episodes.overview: Kiara, Doc's new Kaleidoscope suffered from a severe dizzy spell after Chilly accidentally fell causing her to crash on the floor.

episodes.name: Crash Course
episodes.overview: Doc helps a toy taxi cab driver named Tony learn the importance of paying attention to where you are going after he crashes while carrying Sir Kirby and The Wicked King to Lambie's dance recital and loses his wheels in the process.

episodes.name: Luna on the Moon-a
episodes.overview: When Doc's new space doll, Luna 2200 (which she won as first prize at the school's science fair) keeps slipping as she tries to climb her lunar mountain set, Doc discovers that the sticky grip on Luna's space boot is missing and replaces it for her after discovering the missing pad on Stuffy's back.

episodes.name: Fully in Focus
episodes.overview: Doc gives her viewmaster toy Viewy Stewie an eye exam and discovers that two of his discs are accidentally jammed together causing him to see images incorrectly.

episodes.name: Picky Nikki
episodes.overview: Doc and the toys help Nikki Nickel, a piggybank who only likes shiny coins, see that trying something new can be fun after Doc tries to put a dollar bill into the bank and Nikki refuses to accept it.

episodes.name: Getting to the Heart of Things
episodes.overview: After Doc discovers that Coach Kay, a small plastic doll in a football/soccer kit has a crack in her whistle valve, she takes her to the clinic to perform "surgery" to replace the valve but needed to confirm Kay that everything is going to be alright after she became afraid of the Surgery procedures and prepping up.

episodes.name: Toy in the Sun
episodes.overview: Doc and the toys learn an important lesson about sun exposure after Donny accidentally leaves Bronty outside buried in the garden while playing "Dig the Dino" and his back was exposed to the sun and his plastic becomes discolored.

episodes.name: Slip 'N Slide
episodes.overview: At the park's wading pool, Stuffy wishes he could go in the wading pool with the other pool toys. But while playing "Splash N' Dodge" with Bronty, Stuffy slips and fell into the wading pool causing his plush to get all soggy.

episodes.name: A Big Pain in Teddy's Tummy
episodes.overview: While Donny is playing in the Rose bushes with Lambie, Chilly and Teddy B, Donny gets prickled by accident. While Doc investigates, Teddy B. fears that he had hurt Donny, and he doesn't want to play with him again, and runs away. Teddy B later realizes that he has a sharp pain in his tummy, the result of a Rose thorn that was stuck in him, that prickled both Donny and Doc.

episodes.name: Boxed In
episodes.overview: Flora, a Flamenco dancing doll that Doc received as a gift from her Grandmother who was visiting Spain, is having a ball thrown in her honor by Doc and company, but for some unknown reason doesn't want to come out the box. Doc soon discovers that Flora has a fear of getting messy, that she must overcome.

episodes.name: Itty Bitty Bess Takes Flight
episodes.overview: Itty Bitty Bess and her airplane Queenie (a antique tintype airplane pilot which Doc's mom got from a Flea Market/Swap Meet who was based on "Queen" Bessie Coleman a famous aviator who was the first African American woman to receive an international pilot license) has trouble flying due to rust. So Doc and the crew must help Bess get back into the Wild Blue Yonder.

episodes.name: Top Lamb
episodes.overview: Clarence, a cardboard bat, accidentally gets wet, so he is unable to stand; Rockstar Ruby's microphone button breaks, Ruby is crushed and can't do her show the right way.

episodes.name: Molly Molly Mouthful
episodes.overview: Doc's toy "Molly Molly Mouthful" loves to have flapjacks flipped into her mouth. When Molly-Molly comes to life and keeps talking while eating, one of her plastic flapjacks gets stuck in her mouth, so Doc and the crew teach Molly-Molly how to eat carefully and not to talk with her mouth full.

episodes.name: Filling Chilly
episodes.overview: While playing Buccaneers with Doc and the crew, Chilly accidentally rips himself and loses half his stuffing, so Doc has to replace Chilly's stuffing with cotton balls.

episodes.name: Doc's Dream Team
episodes.overview: As Doc's dad reads a bedtime story about Prince Cameron and the giant five-eyed purple monster to her, Doc falls asleep and has a nightmare about the five-eyed purple monster chasing after her, so the toys decide to help Doc overcome her nightmare.

episodes.name: A Dragon's Best Friend
episodes.overview: Doc and the crew are playing Hide and Seek at the park when Stuffy finds a odd little toy critter who develops a crush on Stuffy. So Doc and the crew decide to adopt the critter, now named Squibbles, as Stuffy's new toy pet.

episodes.name: Take Your Pet to the Vet
episodes.overview: The toys prepare to welcome Coleslaw, Doc's class hamster from school who loves to roll around in her Hamster ball. When Coleslaw falls ill, Doc and her mom take Coleslaw to Dr. Reese's Vet Clinic and discover that Coleslaw has a slight cold and needs to rest.

episodes.name: Master and Commander
episodes.overview: Commander Crush and Star Blazer Zero are playing Space Commander, but Commander Crush injures himself while falling off his chair, and learns the importance of keeping all four legs of the chair on the ground.

episodes.name: Stuffy and Squibbles
episodes.overview: Stuffy learns that it's very important to take care of Squibbles, especially when Squibbles runs out of energy and needed to be recharged.

episodes.name: Queen of Thrones
episodes.overview: As the toys are playing Musical Thrones, Stuffy accidentally knocks down The Wicked King's & Queen Amina's castle. When they are rebuilding the castle her bossiness causes a rift with the toys and they hurt Queen Amina's feelings by calling her 'bossy.' The toys learn that Queen Amina isn't bossy but is doing her job as a leader.

episodes.name: Huggable Hallie
episodes.overview: During a check-up, Hallie's foot mysteriously starts to talk, making the other toys think that Hallie's foot is possessed. But it is discovered that the voice chip that makes Hallie talk went down to her foot and needs surgery to remove it.

episodes.name: Pop-Up Paulo
episodes.overview: Pop Up Paulo a pop-up toy frog that Donny received in a Goodie Bag injures himself but Doc and the others thinks that Pop Up Paulo is faking it and don't realize that he is really injured.

episodes.name: Nurse's Office
episodes.overview: As Doc and the toys are playing School, Chilly decides to pretend to be sick so he can visit the Nurse's Office but discovers that he can't fake a illness just to visit the Nurse's Office.

episodes.name: A Case of the Glitters
episodes.overview: As Doc and the toys were playing Explorers the toys came down with a mysterious outbreak that is making the toys itchy. It was discovered that the toys had an outbreak of the glitters due to wearing Dress Up Daisy's explorer hat after glitter was spilled on her, similar to head lice. Later even after being cleaned they are afraid to play with Dress Up Daisy and hurt her feelings in the process.

episodes.name: Doc McStuffins Goes to Washington
episodes.overview: Doc and her toys receive an invite to The White House in Washington DC to meet with First Lady Michelle Obama, but as they prepare for a tour of The White House, Lisa (one of the other children invited)'s toy otter Tavia falls ill and goes "MIA" at the White House and it's up to Doc and the toys to find Tavia.

episodes.name: Winded Winnie
episodes.overview: It's Donny's birthday but Winnie a toy tiger cub that is used to blow up balloons isn't working properly. Doc discovers that Winnie has dust in her lungs due to being up in the attic for a long time and needs to clear out her lungs to blow up balloons properly.

episodes.name: Hallie Halloween
episodes.overview:
Doc decides to open a new veterinarian branch to her clinic to help Donny's new toy, Findo, a robot puppy.

In a rush to perform a show for Doc and the toys, one of the Twirly Twins accidentally puts on her magnetic boots upside-down and isn't able to perform her tricks correctly.

episodes.name: Don't Fence Me In
episodes.overview: Gustav the Gulpy Gulpy Gator gets himself stuck in a fence gate while chasing a runaway marble, and Doc and the other toys try to set Gustav free without injuring him in the process.

episodes.name: Dmitri the Dazzling!
episodes.overview: Donny's magician partner, Dmitri's toy bunny-rabbit Carrots gets a loose spring in its paw and accidentally wrecks Dmitri's Magic Stage in the process.

episodes.name: Smitten With a Kitten
episodes.overview: Doc receives a toy kitten as a gift at a second-hand-toy fund-raiser at her school, who Lambie decides to adopt and names Whispers. At first, the kitten feels intimidated, but gets used to its surroundings and its new owner, Lambie.

episodes.name: The Search for Squibbles
episodes.overview: As Stuffy, Dress Up Daisy and her pet poodle Piper were training Sqibbles, Squibbles goes AWOL, and its up to Doc and the other toys to find the missing Squibbles.

episodes.name: Factory Fabulous
episodes.overview: The Logger of Lemurs troupe (Wyatt, Trixie, Butch, Calamity, Otis, Tumbleweed, Boots, Maybelle, Cheyenne and Yul) show off their amazing skills to Oooey Gablooey. The yellow male lemur Wyatt discovers that he is missing an arm and decided to quit the team. Doc researches that Wyatt was actually intentionally built this way at the factory. She tells him he is perfect the way he is, that being born with one arm is great because it is unduplicatable, and makes him one of a kind.

episodes.name: Lambie Gets the Linties
episodes.overview: As Professor Hootsburg plans to paint a portrait of the "plushies", Lambie falls into a mud puddle while doing a pirouette and gets muddy and cannot participate in the portrait. In the meanwhile the Wicked King tries to Photobomb the portrait. As Lambie returns, she discovers that she has lint all over her body and needs surgery to remove the lint from her plush.

episodes.name: Moo-Moo's Tutu Boo Boo
episodes.overview: Moo Moo always dreamed to be a ballet dancer like Bella and Lambie, but Moo Moo accidentally ripped her leg during rehearsal after tripping.

episodes.name: The New Nurse
episodes.overview: Dress-Up Declan, Emmie's fashion doll, visits Doc's home and as they are playing basketball, Hallie injures herself crashing into a rose bush. Luckily, Declan has a Nurse's outfit to assist Doc, but Daisy feels a little chauvinistic about Declan being a nurse. When Daisy injures herself while playing Cowboy, she realizes that Guys like Declan can be nurses, too.

episodes.name: Chilly's Loose Button
episodes.overview: While preparing for a Snowday, Chilly accidentally crashes with Lambie, causing his button on his tummy to become loose, but is afraid to tell Doc.

episodes.name: Say It Again, Sadie
episodes.overview: Emmie's new toy parrot, Sadie, refuses to talk, so Doc takes Sadie in for a check up and discovers that there's a switch on Sadie's back that causes her beak to glow red and makes her speak.

episodes.name: Mind Over Matter
episodes.overview: Salt Water Serge felt out of place being a sea explorer in the middle of a space adventure with Commander Crush and his space crew and felt envious of the flashy toys. Donny took the Command Center to his play date, and Salt Water Serge showed the others how they could still play Space Explorers without all the fancy gadgetry.

episodes.name: Snowy Gablooey
episodes.overview: During a snowball fight with Doc, Donny accidentally got snow in his coat and as he went inside, he accidentally left Oooey Gablooey in a snowdrift causing him to freeze up.

episodes.name: Goooooal!
episodes.overview: As Doc and the toys were playing Ice Hockey, Sir Kirby, who was the star goalie for Hallie's team, accidentally dislocated his shoulder colliding with Tremaine on the ice, but was afraid to tell Doc about it, and had to sit out of the match, and was replaced by Leilani as goalie.

episodes.name: Space Buddies Forever!
episodes.overview: As Doc and the toys were playing Space Exploration, the Wicked King gets abducted by a crow. As Commander Crush rescues the Wicked King, he dislocates his wing, so he can't transform into a space plane until his wing is repaired. Luckily Star Blazer Zero donated two of his screws to repair Commander Crush's wing.

episodes.name: Liv Long and Pawsper
episodes.overview: Luna's robotic dog, Space Rover Olivia 0-197-0, a.k.a. Liv, broke her antenna, but felt uncomfortable as her antenna was replaced, and needed a cone collar to prevent from scratching her antenna.

episodes.name: Kirby's Derby
episodes.overview: Sir Kirby dreams of winning the McStuffins Derby cup and Rose Crown against the Wicked King, Queen Amina and Dress-Up Daisy, but a mishap on Sir Kirby's steed Bonnie Blue (who cracked and lost a wheel on the process) nearly injures Bonnie Blue and caused Sir Kirby to feel guilty about her injury.

episodes.name: Ticklish Truck
episodes.overview: While playing "Defend the Pillow Fort from the Dragons," a pillow rips, spewing feathers all over the room, but one of the feathers gets imbedded inside Lenny causing him to laugh and squirt water uncontrollably.

episodes.name: Blast Off to the Unknown!
episodes.overview: Donny's friend Carlos is moving away and his space toy Star Blazer Zero is going with him and Star Blazer Zero is sad about leaving the neighborhood and his best friend, Commander Crush and is afraid about going to a unknown place. But Doc assures Star Blazer Zero that it's okay to be sad and not to be nervous in discovering new places.

episodes.name: Bust a Move
episodes.overview: A new neighbor named Dawn moves into Carlos' old home in the neighborhood and brings her stuffed toy dancing pig Ferris along, but Ferris is banged up and dirty from the move. As Doc gives Ferris a check-up, Commander Crush wonders if Ferris could become friends with him. Luckily, both Ferris and Commander Crush has one thing in common-they love to dance-and became good friends.

episodes.name: Baby McStuffins
episodes.overview: Doc's mom and dad, announce that she and Donny will be getting a younger sibling, as they will be adopting a baby in a couple months. In the meantime, she gives Doc a baby doll to practice taking care of to prove she is ready to babysit. After a slew of nicknames, Doc accepts Chilly's suggestion of "Cutie Cute", but abbreviates it, naming her "Cece McStuffins".

episodes.name: Selfless Snowman
episodes.overview: Doc holds a stuffing donation drive after Hallie realizes their stockpile is running low. Chilly doesn't want to donate since he's afraid of the pain. He changes his mind after Pickles the bunny receives a rip in her plush. She needs a rare kind of stuffing which only he can provide, so he offers up his inner whiteness to fill her void.

episodes.name: St. Patrick's Day Dilemma
episodes.overview: Doc brings home a new paper doll named Fiona for St. Patrick's Day and when Donny draws on her, her dress doesnt look good.

episodes.name: A Giant Save
episodes.overview: Doc's mom gives her a giant named Gillian (from the book), but she doesnt know how to have a tea party and build a castle. In the meanwhile, Professor Hootsburgh gets stuck in a tree (who rips herself in the process) and Gillian saves her.

episodes.name: Runaway Love
episodes.overview: When Donny runs away who thinks the baby will take his place, it's up to Doc and her parents to find him.

episodes.name: Tour De McStuffins
episodes.overview: When Doc wins a toy bike with a racer named Stella, the racer goes too fast and crashes into a block castle and bends her leg in the process.

episodes.name: Hooty's Duty
episodes.overview: Nurse Hattie throws Doc's mom a baby shower.

episodes.name: A Cure For a King
episodes.overview: When the Wicked King steals Queen Amina's crown, he loses his own crown in the process.

episodes.name: Bringing Home Baby
episodes.overview: Doc's mom, gets the call - Baby McStuffins is here! They rush to meet and retrieve the baby and Grandma McStuffins comes to take care of Donny and Doc.

episodes.name: Baby Names
episodes.overview: The McStuffins family chooses a name for the new baby: Maya. Also, Lala, the new baby toy ripped her plush and Doc fixes her in the process.

episodes.name: Night Night, Lala
episodes.overview: The new baby toy, Lala, has a hard time adjusting to her new home.

episodes.name: The Lady in the Lake
episodes.overview: When Dress-Up Daisy doesn't want to wear her life vest on the boat, she falls in the water and gets soaked.

episodes.name: Black Belt Kangaroos
episodes.overview: Sydney the kangaroo has a hard time concentrating on his karate lesson and injures himself in the process.

episodes.name: Joni the Pony
episodes.overview: Joni the pony trips over her mane and the other toys suggest a haircut.

episodes.name: Sleepless in Stuffyland
episodes.overview: Stuffy can't sleep the night before Doc's Presentation at school.

episodes.name: The Scrapiest Dragon
episodes.overview: Stuffy scrapes his belly during a ping pong match with Hallie.

episodes.name: Going for Broke
episodes.overview: Awesome Guy tries to compete in every event of the McStuffins Toyathalon.

episodes.name: Welcome to McStuffinsville
episodes.overview: Docs grandmother transports Doc to the magical world of McStuffinsville where she will carry on a family tradition by expanding her practice to the McStuffins Toy Hospital. There, on her first day as chief resident, Doc must tend to Stanley, a lonely, brokenhearted toy.

episodes.name: First Day of Med School
episodes.overview: Doc enlists Lambie, Stuffy, and Chilly as Toy Med Students to help her take care of all of the patients at McStuffins Toy Hospital.

episodes.name: Stuffy Gets His Scrubs
episodes.overview: Doc appoints Stuffy head of the Vet Clinic at McStuffins Toy Hospital.

episodes.name: Night Shift
episodes.overview: On their first night shift, Lambie is in charge of the Hospital Nursery but cannot get the babies to sleep.

episodes.name: Check-Up Chilly
episodes.overview: Chilly schedules too many appointments for himself.

episodes.name: Project Nursery Makeover
episodes.overview: Doc and the toys receive 4 identical toy babies as Lambie has a problem telling the babies apart.

episodes.name: Stuffy's Ambulance Ride
episodes.overview: As Stuffy hurts himself playing a jousting match, he fears his first ambulance ride to the hospital.

episodes.name: Made to Be a Nurse
episodes.overview: A new nurse upstages Hallie and she no longer feels needed.

episodes.name: Rescue at the Ranch
episodes.overview: Doc responds to an emergency call during an accident at Southwest Sal's Ranch. It teaches you the importance of staying calm and following directions.

episodes.name: CeCe's First Bath
episodes.overview: When baby toy Cece gets dirty, Doc and her toys have to get her clean, and they have to do it fast. Doc's baby sister Maya has just woken up from her nap and wants Cece, but she's too dirty to play with, and that makes Maya cry. Doc tries to give Cece a bath, but every time she tries to get her in the water, Cece cries.

episodes.name: The Most Impatient Patient
episodes.overview: After getting a crown-cussion, the Wicked King turns into a difficult patient.

episodes.name: Chilly's Snow Globe Shakeup
episodes.overview: Doc and her toys travel to the Giant Snow Globe outside McStuffinsville to help one of the Snow Peeps.

episodes.name: Hoarse Hallie
episodes.overview: Hallie is so excited after being chosen to sing the opening song for the Foosball Game, she over-practices and loses her voice.

episodes.name: A Lesson in Diagnosis
episodes.overview: The Toy Med students must learn how to diagnose a patient without Doc's help.

episodes.name: Karaoke Katie's Opening Night
episodes.overview: The toys learn about bedside manner as they take care of Karaoke Katie, a doll who is disappointed about having to cancel her show because her batteries won't hold a charge.

episodes.name: Nikki's Night in the E.R.
episodes.overview: After her bank gets a crack in it, Nikki Nickel needs to stay at the hospital overnight.

episodes.name: Royal Buddies
episodes.overview: While exploring the Royal Lands, Sir Kirby loses his buddy and gets hurt.

episodes.name: Bouncy House Boo Boos
episodes.overview: When some of the toys get hurt at Bobbys birthday party, Doc teaches them about bounce house safety.

episodes.name: The Best Therapy Pet Yet
episodes.overview: While Hazel is in the hospital, Stuffy tries to sneak Squibbles in to cheer her up.

episodes.name: The Mayor's Speech
episodes.overview: When Mayor Billingtons beak gets jammed during a speech, Doc teaches him that speech impediments are nothing to be embarrassed about.

episodes.name: The Lake Monster
episodes.overview: After hearing theres a monster in Bathtub Lake, Doc and the toys go to investigate.

episodes.name: Chuck Learns to Look!
episodes.overview: When Chuck, the wind-up chicken, crosses the street without looking, he unintentionally causes accidents.

episodes.name: Birthday Party Emergency
episodes.overview: When Doc and the toys discover a broken birthday present, they rush to fix it before its child returns.

episodes.name: Camille Gets Over the Hump
episodes.overview: When Camille, a toy camel, gets hurt, its up to Doc and the other Med Students to convince her to go to the hospital.

episodes.name: Willow's Wonky Whiskers
episodes.overview: When Doc is unable to see inside a toys fluffy cheek, she decides to do a CAT scan to figure out the problem.

episodes.name: Into the Hundred Acre Wood
episodes.overview: Doc McStuffins and her toys meet Winnie the Pooh and his friends.

episodes.name: Mole Money, Mole Problems
episodes.overview: When a toy mole is having trouble getting around without bumping into everything, Doc diagnoses her and calls on Stuffy to find her a guide pet.

episodes.name: Yip, Yip, Boom
episodes.overview: During the light show finale, Squibbles gets scared and runs amok through McStuffinsville.

episodes.name: Get-Well Gus Gets Well
episodes.overview: When flying Pegasus toy Get-Well Gus crashes and breaks off one of his wings, Doc outfits him with a prosthetic.

episodes.name: Triceratops Trouble
episodes.overview: Doc and the toys have trouble diagnosing a triceratops train that cant get enough traction to move.

episodes.name: Hannah the Brave
episodes.overview: When Hannah the doll gets gum stuck in her hair, she needs Doc's help

episodes.name: Waddly's Huggy Overload
episodes.overview: Doc is selected to lead the rescue workers parade.

episodes.name: Lambie Stuffy Switcharoo
episodes.overview: When Stuffy claims that Lambie's job taking care of the babies in the Toy Nursery is easy, Lambie challenges him to switch jobs with her for the day.

episodes.name: The Sleepwalking King
episodes.overview: During a sleepover at the Royal Castle, Doc discovers the Wicked King has been sleepwalking.

episodes.name: Count Clarence's Daytime Adventure
episodes.overview: Count Clarence decides to stay up past his bedtime and learns that becoming over-tired is not good for him

episodes.name: Dixie Gets Glued
episodes.overview: A new baby doll toy named Dixie creates a mess after getting into some art supplies and covering herself with glue.

episodes.name: Lambie and the McStuffins Babies
episodes.overview: Lambie and the other toys visit Baby Doll Headquarters where they help deliver some new baby toys to the Nursery.

episodes.name: The Emergency Plan
episodes.overview: Doc helps reunite members of a doll family and shows them how to make emergency kits after they get separated during an earthquake caused by Dragon-Bot jumping up and down

episodes.name: What a Quack
episodes.overview: A toy duck tries fixing other toys without the proper training.

episodes.name: First Responders to the Rescue
episodes.overview: After a sudden storm hits McStuffinsville, a young boy named Dev finds himself transported to the town along with his toys who come together to form the First Responders team.

episodes.name: Mermaid in the Midfield
episodes.overview: Doc teaches the toys about toy sports medicine during a Foosball Championship game.

episodes.name: Whole Lotta Hula
episodes.overview: When Leilani been hulaing in the sun too long, she decide to not go to the sun again.

episodes.name: Daisy Makes the Call
episodes.overview: Dressup Daisy makes too many emergency calls.

episodes.name: Visiting Hours
episodes.overview: When Commander Crush gets into a bike crash, Star Blazer Zero comes to visit him while he was recovering at the Toy Hosiptal.

episodes.name: On a Roll!
episodes.overview: Wildlife Will has problems traveling in McStuffinsville due to his wheelchair from gates, stairs and high areas.

episodes.name: Home Is Where the Fruit Is
episodes.overview: A lost toy Porcupine named Rocky wanders off too far from home as Doc, Officer Pete and the toys search for Rocky's home.

episodes.name: Stuffy's Wild Pet
episodes.overview: While on Safari, Stuffy decides to adopt a toy zebra.

episodes.name: On Call Ball
episodes.overview: Lambie gets an invitation to the Wicked King's "Ball-a-Thon," an all night dance competition.

episodes.name: The Pet Rescue Team
episodes.overview: When Stuffy wants to join the First Responders after seeing them save the day, Doc suggests they start a rescue team to save pets while the First Responders are busy!

episodes.name: A Pet for Everyone
episodes.overview: When Stuffy wants to join the First Responders after seeing them save the day, Doc suggests they start a rescue team to save pets while the First Responders are busy!

episodes.name: The Doc McStuffins Christmas Special
episodes.overview: When Santa Claus goes missing, it's up to Doc and the Pet Rescue Team to deliver all of the presents for all of the kids in the world before Christmas Day.

episodes.name: Toys in Space
episodes.overview: After Chilly accidentally blasts off on Luna's rocket to an unexplored planet, it's up to Doc and her friends to bring him and Luna's robot dog, Liv, back home to McStuffinsville.

episodes.name: Adventures in Baby Land
episodes.overview: When Cece accidentally gets hold of Lambie's Toysponder and transports herself to McStuffinsville, Doc and the gang must embark on a rollicking adventure to find her.

episodes.name: Stuffy's Safari
episodes.overview: Stuffy ventures deep into the jungle in search of Dragon Mountain, a legendary place where he hopes to find a dragon family of his own.

episodes.name: Jungle Jumble
episodes.overview: After offering to watch over the Nursery, Chilly is too afraid to ask questions and gets in way over his head.

episodes.name: Arctic Exposure
episodes.overview: To save Scarlet's dad, Doc and her friends must venture where no McStuffins toy has gone before: to the Toyarctic!

episodes.name: Jumbo Mumbo
episodes.overview: Chilly forms a special bond with Mumbo, a rambunctious baby mammoth; when Mumbo is ready to be delivered to the Toyartic, Chilly must find a way for them to remain friends.

episodes.name: The Hallie Trap
episodes.overview: When Hallie switches places with her look-alike, the famous Hallie the Entertainer, she learns firsthand what it's like to be a star and what happens when one pretends to be someone else.

episodes.name: Lost & Found
episodes.overview: When Lambie is mistakenly transported to Lost and Found Land, it's up to Doc and the gang to save Lambie and find homes for all the misplaced toys stranded in this forgotten world.

episodes.name: Bedazzled!
episodes.overview: Doc and her friends venture deep into the jungle to find a bedazzling jewel that will help the Duchess of Dazzle regain her strength.

episodes.name: The Great McStuffins Meltdown
episodes.overview: When Doc approves an upgrade to the hospital, she has no idea that the electricity the new machines use will melt the snow in the Toyarctic and endanger her Arctic friends.

episodes.name: It's a Hard Doc Life
episodes.overview: After making a big mistake at the McStuffinsville Toy Hospital, Doc begins to wonder if her patients would have been better off if she hadn't been there at all.
